==Short Description==

The main goal of Digipharm is to foster the dispersion of value-based healthcare by overcoming infrastructural, administrative and data management barriers using blockchain technology (see [[#Additional Information|Additional Information]] for a definition of value-based healthcare).<ref name=„whitepaper“/> In order to achieve this, Digipharm launched several projects of which two are to be released in summer 2018 before their ICO takes place.<ref name=„website“/> The first project, called Reimburse, aims to create a platform based on a private blockchain where self-executing smart contracts can be deployed to enable real time application of value-based pricing models. Thereby, various middlemen standing between healthcare providers, payers (e.g. insurances) and manufacturers can be circumvented leading to higher efficiencies and less administrative costs which facilitates the implementation of value-based pricing. Their second product is called Digihealth, an application that enables patients to access personalized health information and allows them to connect to other patients all over the world. Additionally, patients are encouraged to participate in health-related research by the implementation of a reward system. The use of a private blockchain as the systems’ ledger helps to ensure privacy of sensitive data. However, Digipharm initiates an ICO where the ERC-20 Digipharm token will be sold publicly. Once launched, the token can be used for payments within the Digipharm platform.<ref name=„whitepaper“/> Future projects include Insights (a database for real world evidence), Myhealth (a database for health insurance companies that provides data on patients behavior) and Evolve (a crowdfunding platform for medical innovation).<ref name=„solutions“>https://digipharm.io/solutions.html, accessed on 19.07.2018.</ref>

